        "content": "<p>Hello!<br>\nI was working to add <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/1209\"><code>AtomicFlag</code></a> for the binder driver. </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Should we place this to <code>rust/kernel/sync/atomic.rs</code> (LKMM <code>AtomicBool</code> equivalent) or should it remain specific to driver itself?</li>\n<li>The binder driver would only use <code>load</code>/<code>store</code> methods in <code>binder/rust_binder_main.rs</code> and <code>binder/transaction.rs</code>. Should the implementation initially provide these two methods only, and extend when needed?</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 565676771,
        "sender_full_name": "Ritvik Gupta",
        "timestamp": 1767017652
    },
    {
        "content": "<ol>\n<li>Yes, <code>AtomicFlag</code> goes in <code>rust/kernel</code></li>\n<li>Yes</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 565677215,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767017816
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks :)</p>",
